  <div class="container">
    <section id="about">
      <h2>About Hinju Gonpa</h2>
      <p>Hinju Gonpa, located in Hinju village, was founded by the late Gyen Komchok Thinles. It is affiliated with the Lamayuru Monastery of the Drikung Kagyu School of Buddhism. This sacred site offers a serene environment for spiritual seekers and travelers alike.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="village">
      <h2>About Hinju Village</h2>
      <p>Hinju is a small and peaceful hamlet with just 21 houses, located approximately 130 km from Leh city and 28 km from its Tehsil, Khaltsi. The village is a notable stop on the trekking route from Lamayuru to Chilling and also on the path to Tsomoriri. It is surrounded by dramatic mountains and natural beauty.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="events">
      <h2>Festivals and Events</h2>
      <div class="event">
        <strong>Annual Prayer Ceremony</strong>
        <p>Held in the summer, villagers gather to offer prayers and celebrate with traditional songs and offerings.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="event">
        <strong>Losar (Tibetan New Year)</strong>
        <p>Celebrated with rituals and communal gatherings at the Gonpa.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

